Moody's Investors Service Inc said itmay downgrade 215 mln dlrs of debt of Caesars World Inc and itsunit Caesars World Finance Corp.    Moody's said the review was prompted by the recent bid byinvestor Martin Sosnoff to acquire control of the company.While Sosnoff's bid depends on several factors, includinglicensing by both the Nevada and New Jersey gaming commissions,the deal could result in a significant increase in CaesarsWorld's leverage, the rating agency said.    Caesars currently carries B-1 convertible debt and thefinance has same-rated subordinated debentures. Reuter&#3;